Introduction

PRIMROSE (Korean: 프림로즈) is a four-member South Korean girl group under AO Entertainment. The group started as a duo and debuted on January 13, 2023, with the mini album "Red Moon".

On March 23, 2023, the agency announced that due to personal and health issues, Yeum has parted ways with AO Entertainment and PRIMROSE. The duo would temporarily become a solo act until they found a new member.

Following Yeum’s exit, PRIMROSE welcomed two new members: former HOT ISSUE member Nahyun and former bugAboo member Rainie, A.O Entertainment confirmed on May 3 and May 16, 2023, respectively.

The agency revealed on June 22 that PRIMROSE had finalized their new lineup with Hayun as the last addition and that they were gearing up for a comeback. PRIMROSE dropped their second mini album "Laffy Taffy" on August 18, 2023.
